snippet.textDisplay: Folks, while it is true that Amir Khusro adopted raga Bahar in his sufi renditions, Raga Bahar and Basant are older than Amir Khusro time. Lyrics are NOT Khusro's. They are of Bahadur Shah Zaffer, who used his pen name Ashiq Rang for his hindawi/poorbi poetry. Therefore the correct verse (rendered by old school Qawals): "Nijamudin k derwazay pe awan keh gaiy Ashiq Rang, oure beet gaiy barson.........sakal bun phool....."
snippet.textOriginal: Folks, while it is true that Amir Khusro adopted raga Bahar in his sufi renditions, Raga Bahar and Basant are older than Amir Khusro time. Lyrics are NOT Khusro's. They are of Bahadur Shah Zaffer, who used his pen name Ashiq Rang for his hindawi/poorbi poetry. Therefore the correct verse (rendered by old school Qawals): "Nijamudin k derwazay pe awan keh gaiy Ashiq Rang, oure beet gaiy barson.........sakal bun phool....."
